title: Clinical Companion for Medical-Surgical Nursing Patient-Centered
description:
Authors: Donna D. Ignatavicius MS RN-C ANEF, Kathy A. Hausman PhD RNC, Christine Winkelman, M. Linda Workman PhD RN FAAN
The Clinical Companion for Ignatavicius & Workman: Medical-Surgical Nursing: Critical Thinking for Collaborative Care is an easy-to-use, A-Z guide to 240 common medical-surgical conditions and their management. Written in reader-friendly, direct-address style, this handbook is a convenient quick reference that students can carry with them on clinical days.
